# TypeScript Standards

Consult official references when unsure — see `documentation-references.mdc`:

- [W3Schools TypeScript Best Practices](https://www.w3schools.com/typescript/typescript_best_practices.php)
- [TypeScript Handbook: Do's and Don'ts](https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/declaration-files/do-s-and-don-ts.html)

## Strictness

- Enable `strict` in all `tsconfig.json` files
- No `any` — use `unknown` and narrow, or define proper types
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes; `type` for unions, intersections, and utilities
- Use `satisfies` when inferring a literal type while checking against a wider type

## Types & Domain Modeling

- Model Fiber RPC request/response shapes in `packages/shared` or `packages/fiber-rpc`
- Use branded types for domain IDs when ambiguity is risky (e.g. `ChannelId`, `Pubkey`)
- Export types alongside functions; consumers should not duplicate shapes

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — explicit, shared
export interface ChannelInfo {
  channelId: string;
  capacity: bigint;
  localBalance: bigint;
}

// ❌ BAD — implicit any, duplicated inline
function parseChannel(data: any) { ... }
```

## Error Handling

- Use typed errors or Result patterns for RPC failures; never swallow errors
- Wrap low-level errors with context: method name, params (sanitized), node URL
- Surface user-friendly messages in UI; log technical detail separately

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
catch (error) {
  throw new FiberRpcError('list_channels failed', { cause: error, method: 'list_channels' });
}
```

## Async & Data

- Prefer `async/await` over raw `.then()` chains
- Use `bigint` for on-chain amounts and channel balances — never `number` for token values
- Validate external JSON at boundaries (RPC responses); trust types only after parsing

## Imports & Modules

- Use path aliases consistently (`@fiberguard/shared`, etc.) once configured
- No default exports for utilities — named exports aid tree-shaking and refactoring
- Colocate tests as `*.test.ts` next to source files

## Naming

- `camelCase` for variables/functions; `PascalCase` for types/components
- RPC method wrappers: verb matching Fiber API (`listChannels`, `sendPayment`)
- React components: `PascalCase`; hooks: `use` prefix (`useNodeHealth`)
